1.Introduction

This project is a console-based Library Management System implemented in Python. The system allows the administrator to manage books, members, and book issuing/returning processes.
Through this project, we learned modular programming, file handling, and system design.

2. Problem Statement

Traditional library management using manual registers or Excel sheets is time-consuming, error-prone, and not scalable. There is a need for a lightweight, simple digital solution to efficiently manage book inventory and borrowing records.

3. Objectives

To create a functional and efficient library management system

To automate book storage and issuing process

To maintain member details and borrowing history

To practice Python file handling and modular development

4. Functional Requirements

✔ Add new books
✔ View and search books
✔ Register new library members
✔ Issue books
✔ Return books
✔ Display issued book records

5. Non-Functional Requirements

✔ Usability — Simple and easy to operate
✔ Reliability — Data stored in persistent files
✔ Maintainability — Modular code
✔ Performance — Fast execution even with large data
✔ Scalability — Can be extended to DB or GUI

