7. Implementation Details

Programming Language: Python
Storage: File-based (.txt files)
Modules:

main.py — main menu & navigation

book.py — add/search/display books

member.py — register/display members

issue_return.py — issue & return system

storage.py — data saving/loading (file handling)

data/books.txt — book database

data/members.txt — member database

data/issued.txt — issued book database

8. Testing Approach
Test Case	Input	Expected Output	Result
Add Book	ID=101	Book added	PASS
Add Member	ID=501	Member added	PASS
Issue Book	Book=101, Member=501	Issued successfully	PASS
Return Book	Book=101	Book returned	PASS
Search Book	Title=“Atomic”	Matches displayed	PASS

9. Challenges Faced

Handling string formatting in .txt files

Avoiding duplicate IDs

Case-sensitive file naming (data vs Data)

Modularizing code into multiple files

10o. Learnings

Python file I/O

Data persistence

Designing maintainable code

Working with multiple modules

Using GitHub for version control

Professional project documentation

11. Future Enhancements

Graphical User Interface (Tkinter / Web UI)

Database implementation using MySQL or SQLite

User authentication (admin / staff)

Advanced reporting & analytics

12. Conclusion

The Library Management System successfully fulfills the intended purpose of maintaining and automating library operations. This project demonstrates Python programming skills, systematic design, documentation, and real-world application development.

